A PROGRAM FOR ALIGNING SENTENCES IN BILINGUAL CORPORA William A. Gale Kenneth W. Church AT&T Bell Laboratories 600 Mountain Avenue Murray Hill, NJ, 07974 ABSTRACT Researchers in both machine Iranslation (e.g. , Brown et al. , 1990) and bilingual lexicography (e.g. , Klavans and Tzoukermann, 1990) have recently become interested in studying parallel texts, texts such as the Canadian Hansards (parliamentary proceedings) which are available in multiple languages (French and English). 
